---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

import {getBrandCharts} from "../lib/content/brand-charts";
const charts=getBrandCharts();
---
<BaseLayout title="Goalie Pad Sizing Calculator & Brand Charts | Goalie Gear Fit" description="Find your goalie leg-pad size using reviewed Bauer, CCM, TRUE, Warrior and Brian's charts, then verify the fit at the knee block." dateModified="2026-07-20">
 <section class="home-hero"><div class="hero-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Independent goalie pad sizing</p><h1>Find your goalie pad size by brand.</h1><p class="hero-tagline">Land your knee. <em>Not a guess.</em></p><p class="lede">Match your measurements against reviewed manufacturer rules, then take the result onto the ice for the only check that matters.</p><p class="hero-actions"><a class="button" href="/calculator">Find my pad size <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a><a class="text-link" href="/guides/how-to-measure-goalie-pads">How to measure <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></p><p class="hero-proof"><span>5 brands reviewed</span><span>No nearest-size guesses</span><span>Sources shown</span></p></div><div class="crease-visual" aria-hidden="true"><div class="crease-visual__net"></div><div class="crease-visual__pad crease-visual__pad--left"></div><div class="crease-visual__pad crease-visual__pad--right"></div><p><strong>Knee block</strong><br>Physical fit check</p></div></section>
 <section class="brand-section" aria-labelledby="brand-heading"><div class="section-heading"><div><p class="eyebrow">Reviewed manufacturer data</p><h2 id="brand-heading">Start with the badge on your pad.</h2></div><p>Every brand uses its own chart logic. We keep those differences intact instead of forcing a false universal size.</p></div><div class="brand-grid">{charts.map(chart=><article class="brand-card"><img class:list={["brand-card__logo",{"brand-logo--inverse":chart.vendor.inverseLogo}]} src={chart.vendor.logoPath} alt="" width="140" height="48" loading="lazy"/><div><h3><a href={`/charts/${chart.slug}`}>{chart.brand}</a></h3><p>{chart.rules.length} reviewed rules · {chart.categories.length} chart section{chart.categories.length===1?"":"s"}</p></div><span class="brand-card__arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></article>)}</div><p class="section-action"><a href="/charts/">Compare all brand charts <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></p></section>
 <section class="home-steps" aria-labelledby="steps-heading"><div class="section-heading"><div><p class="eyebrow">The fitting sequence</p><h2 id="steps-heading">From tape measure to crease.</h2></div><p>Three checks. In this order. The calculator narrows the field; your stance confirms the fit.</p></div><ol class="step-grid"><li><span class="step-number">01</span><strong>Measure the right line.</strong><span>Floor-to-knee and ankle-to-knee are not interchangeable.</span></li><li><span class="step-number">02</span><strong>Match the actual chart.</strong><span>Overlaps show adjacent options. Missing evidence stays undetermined.</span></li><li><span class="step-number">03</span><strong>Drop into butterfly.</strong><span>With skates and protection on, confirm your knee lands securely on the block.</span></li></ol></section>
 <section class="trust-section"><div><p class="eyebrow">Why the answer may be “we can’t tell”</p><h2>Honest sizing stops where the chart stops.</h2></div><div><p>The charts come from reviewed manufacturer guidance, and each brand keeps the measurement method it actually publishes. We do not silently convert one method into another or fill missing evidence with a guessed size.</p><p>Use the chart result as a starting point, then verify knee-block landing and overall pad movement in your full setup.</p><p class="trust-links"><a href="/methodology">Read our methodology</a><a href="/guides/thigh-rise-and-fit-check">Run the fit check</a></p></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
